---
import { VERSION, BUILD } from '../lib/version';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Distinction as Primitive</title>
  <meta name="description" content="A philosophical meta-theory taking distinction-making as prior to all theorising. Two axioms, a formal treatise, and a living canon of derivations and rulings.">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400&family=Sora:wght@300;400;500;600&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1>Distinction as Primitive</h1>
        <p class="tagline">Reality under resource constraints</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="main-content">
      <section class="intro">
        <p class="lead">
          A philosophical meta-theory with one claim at its core: distinction-making comes before all theorising — first in the order of what can be expressed. From that starting point, two axioms:
        </p>
        <div class="axioms">
          <div class="axiom">
            <span class="axiom-number">A1</span>
            <span class="axiom-text">All distinctions cost energy</span>
          </div>
          <div class="axiom">
            <span class="axiom-number">A2</span>
            <span class="axiom-text">All observers have finite energy budgets</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="consequence">
          From these alone, three things genuinely follow: effective discreteness, resolution limits, and finitude. The rest — quantum uncertainty, entropy, consciousness, spacetime — the framework reads through that lens rather than derives. Keeping the two apart is what keeps the claim honest.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="entry-points">
        <a href="/treatise" class="entry-card treatise">
          <div class="card-icon">
            <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="card-content">
            <h2>The Treatise</h2>
            <p>The main artefact. Ten modules from philosophical foundations to synthesis, every claim labelled — derived, interpreted, or imported. The key contribution domain is learning: Module 4.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-arrow">→</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/intro" class="entry-card intro">
          <div class="card-icon">
            <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z"/>
              <path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"/>
              <path d="M2 12l10 5 10-5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="card-content">
            <h2>Start Here</h2>
            <p>A conversational introduction to the framework. What it is, where it came from, and why it matters.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-arrow">→</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/essay" class="entry-card primary">
          <div class="card-icon">
            <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"/>
              <path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="card-content">
            <h2>Read the Essay</h2>
            <p>The framework as a single narrative in 13 sections — the readable telling, from philosophical foundations through quantum mechanics, consciousness, and spacetime.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-arrow">→</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/explore" class="entry-card secondary">
          <div class="card-icon">
            <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
              <path d="M12 2a14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0 20 14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0-20"/>
              <path d="M2 12h20"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="card-content">
            <h2>Explore Concepts</h2>
            <p>Browse the key propositions as a network of interconnected ideas. Each concept linked to its logical dependencies.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-arrow">→</span>
        </a>
      </section>

      <section class="status-block">
        <div class="status-header">
          <span class="status-label">Where the thesis stands</span>
          <span class="status-badge">V8 · Working Paper</span>
        </div>
        <p class="status-text">
          The thesis now has a canonical statement — a single node assembled in July 2026 from everywhere
          it is stated across the wider work, from the formal treatise to the deployed learning systems it
          grew out of. The flagship derivation, effective discreteness, stands as a theorem of information
          thermodynamics about observers, conditional on a stated model of what an observer is. Three
          derivation chains are complete; a fourth, on learning as optimisation, is in preparation.
        </p>
        <p class="status-text">
          This is a living graph, not a finished text. Contradictions between tellings are surfaced and
          ruled on rather than smoothed over — most recently the ruling that the framework dissolves
          ontology itself, rather than choosing between ontological and expressibility-only readings.
          The core was hardened through sustained systematic adversarial critique; what remains scoped
          or conjectured is flagged as such throughout.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <div class="footer-content">
        <span class="version-info">{VERSION} · build {BUILD}</span>
        <span class="footer-text">Working Paper · July 2026</span>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>

<style>
  :root {
    --void: #0a0a0c;
    --depth-1: #12121a;
    --depth-2: #1a1a24;
    --border: #2a2a3a;
    --text-primary: #e8e8f0;
    --text-secondary: #a0a0b8;
    --text-muted: #606080;
    --accent: #4a9eff;
    --accent-dim: rgba(74, 158, 255, 0.15);
    --font-display: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    --font-body: 'Sora', sans-serif;
    --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
  }

  * {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    background: var(--void);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .container {
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .hero {
    padding: 6rem 2rem 4rem;
    text-align: center;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--depth-1) 0%, var(--void) 100%);
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .tagline {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .main-content {
    flex: 1;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem 4rem;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .intro {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .axioms {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .axiom {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--depth-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .axiom-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-dim);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .axiom-text {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .consequence {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .entry-points {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .entry-card {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    background: var(--depth-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .entry-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--depth-2);
  }

  .entry-card.intro {
    border-color: #f0a050;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--depth-1) 0%, rgba(240, 160, 80, 0.08) 100%);
  }

  .entry-card.intro .card-icon {
    color: #f0a050;
  }

  .entry-card.primary {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--depth-1) 0%, var(--accent-dim) 100%);
  }

  .entry-card.treatise {
    border-color: #50c878;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--depth-1) 0%, rgba(80, 200, 120, 0.08) 100%);
  }

  .entry-card.treatise .card-icon {
    color: #50c878;
  }

  .card-icon {
    color: var(--accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .card-content {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .card-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .card-content p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .card-arrow {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    transition: transform 0.2s;
  }

  .entry-card:hover .card-arrow {
    transform: translateX(4px);
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .status-block {
    background: var(--depth-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .status-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .status-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .status-badge {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #50c878;
    background: rgba(80, 200, 120, 0.15);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .status-text {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .status-text + .status-text {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .site-footer {
    padding: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .footer-content {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .entry-card {
      flex-direction: column;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .card-arrow {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>
